concept.title: CONE Command
concept.shortdesc: Creates a 3D Solid in the shape of a cone.

p.note: In BricsCAD Classic, which doesn’t support 3D solids, the CONE command launches the .

conbody.p: Create a 3D solid in the shape of a circular or elliptical cone. Choose from a combination of options including center, radius, diameter, 3 point, 2 point, tangents, axis endpoints, and height.

section.title: Methods to create a cone
section.p: There are five methods to begin creating a cone:

dlentry.dd: Begin creating a circular cone by specifying the center of the base then:
Specify the radius of the base of the cone.
Additional option: [Diameter]
Specify the height of the cone.
Additional options: [2Point/Axis endpoint/Top radius]
Begin creating a circular cone by specifying the first of three points on the circumference of its base then:
Specify the second point on the circumference.
Specify the third point on the circumference.
Specify the height of the cone.
Additional options: [2Point/Axis endpoint/Top radius]
Begin creating a circular cone by specifying the first of two points on the circumference of its base then:
Specify the second point on the diameter. The two points define the diameter of the base.
Specify the height of the cone.
Additional options: [2Point/Axis endpoint/Top radius]
Begin creating a circular cone by selecting a tangent point on the first entity then:

dlentry.dt: Specify point on object for second tangent
dlentry.dd: Select a tangent point on the second entity.
Specify a valid radius for the base. If you specify a radius that is not possible with the selected tangents, you are prompted to specify the tangents and radius again.
Specify the height of the cone.
Additional options: [2Point/Axis endpoint/Top radius]
Begin creating an elliptical cone by specifying the first end of the ellipse axis then:
Alternate option: [Center]
Specify the second end of the ellipse axis.
Specify the radius of the other ellipse axis.
Specify the height of the cone.
Additional options: [2Point/Axis endpoint/Top radius]

section.title: Options within the CONE command
section.p: After you begin creating a cone, the following options may be available:

dlentry.dd: Specify the height of the cone as the distance between any two points.
Specify the axis endpoint to define the height and orientation of the cone in 3D space. The center of the base is used as the other axis endpoint.
Specify a radius for the top of the cone. Any radius larger than zero (0) creates a cone with a flat top.
Specify the diameter of the cone’s base.
